  "texts": [
    ")Notice that, when the structure group is contained in N L, one recovers the definition of a principal Nbundle.",
    "In that case, there is a natural free right N-action which is transitive on fibres.",
    "A similar thing happens for a twisted principal bundle π: M → B.",
    "Consider a covering {U i } of B and local trivialisationsψ i: M Ui:= π -1 (U i) → U i × N.For each i there is an obvious right free N-action coming from right-multiplication on the second factor: (6)• i: M Ui × N → M Ui, ψ -1 i (b, n) • i n ′ → ψ -1 i (b, n • n ′).",
    "We denote by τ ij: U ij → Aut(N) δ ⋉ N L the transition function on a connected component U ij of U i ∩ U j ̸ = ∅: ψ j • ψ -1 i (b, n) = (b, (τ ij (b))(n)), b ∈ U ij, n ∈ N.Since N L commutes with right-multiplication, there exists φ ij ∈ Aut(N) such that (7)p • i n = p • j φ ij (n), n ∈ N, p ∈ M Uij.The fact that φ ij is independent of b is due to the choice of discrete topology on Aut(N)."
